<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972E66744155DC9E5E" blockId="2.[376,902,275,299]" box="[376,902,275,299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
<heading id="D09FA337FFCBFF972E66744155DC9E5E" bold="true" box="[376,902,275,299]" centered="true" fontSize="8" level="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B91CC849FFCBFF972E66744155DC9E5E" bold="true" box="[376,902,275,299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
<taxonomicName id="4C686FD8FFCBFF972E66744154BF9E5E" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2017" box="[376,741,275,299]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phobos" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B91CC849FFCBFF972E66744157849E5E" bold="true" box="[376,478,275,299]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B91CC849FFCBFF972EF3744154DC9E5E" bold="true" box="[493,646,275,299]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Haplanthaxia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B91CC849FFCBFF972D88744154BF9E5E" bold="true" box="[662,741,275,299]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">phobos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FAB741155059E0F" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C686FD8FFCBFF972FF77411578C9E2E" authority="Bílý, 2017" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2017" box="[233,470,323,347]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phobos" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B91CC849FFCBFF972FF7741157109E2E" box="[233,330,323,347]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B91CC849FFCBFF972E437411572D9E2F" box="[349,375,323,346]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B91CC849FFCBFF972E977411578C9E2E" box="[393,470,323,347]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">phobos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22F7532FFCBFF972EFF7411546D9E2F" box="[481,567,323,346]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
species-group differs from other currently defined species-groups of 
<taxonomicName id="4C686FD8FFCBFF972E47743157B69E0E" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" box="[345,492,355,379]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B91CC849FFCBFF972E47743157B69E0E" box="[345,492,355,379]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Haplanthaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following set of characters:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37247D0FFCBFF972FD274D1544E9BFC" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD274D154D99EEF" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,643,387,410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– rather strongly, regularly convex frons;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD274F152589ECF" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,1026,419,442]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– frontoclypeus not separated from frons by depression or transverse groove;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD2749157259E8F" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– relatively short antennae reaching posterior third of lateral pronotal margins when laid alongside;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD27751557D9D6F" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,807,515,538]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– vertex narrow, 0.9 – 1.0 times as wide as width of eye;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD2777154F89D4F" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,674,547,570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– anterior pronotal margin deeply bisinuate;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD2771155189D0F" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– pronotal sculpture homogeneous consisting of small, dense, regular, rounded or slightly polygonal cells with well-developed central grains;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD277D154AC9DEF" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,758,643,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– lateroposterior pronotal depressions usually wide;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD277F155A59DCF" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,1023,675,698]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
– elytra only very weakly wedge-shaped almost subparallel (
<figureCitation id="135308DEFFCBFF972C4877F155A99DCF" box="[854,1011,675,698]" captionStart="Figs 1–6. 1" captionStartId="4.[153,190,1281,1300]" captionTargetBox="[227,1050,221,1263]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[227,1050,219,1269]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–6. 1 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) phobos sp. nov., holotype, 4.3 mm; 2 – the same, allotype, 3.7 mm; 3 – the same, aedeagus, holotype; 4 – A. (H.) deimos sp. nov., holotype, 4.3 mm; 5 – the same, allotype, 3.7 mm; 6 – the same, aedeagus, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316396" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316396/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Figs. 1–2, 4–5</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD2779155279DAF" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,893,707,730]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– basal, transverse elytral groove very wide, reaching scutellum;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD277B155689D8F" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,818,739,762]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– only the apex of elytra with very fine, lateral serrations;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD2765154EB9C6F" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,689,771,794]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– scutellum almost 1.5 times as long as wide;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD27671559F9C4F" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,965,803,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– legs relatively short, male meso- and metatibiae straight, unmodified;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD27611554A9C2F" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,784,835,858]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– third and fourth tarsomeres pale, distinctly widened;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD2763154969CCF" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
– anal ventrite of both sexes of the same shape, only with very fine lateral serrations; – aedeagus spindle-shaped, apical portion of parameres narrow, apically obliquely truncate, somewhat bent outwards (
<figureCitation id="135308DEFFCBFF972D4376F154E49CCF" box="[605,702,931,954]" captionStart="Figs 1–6. 1" captionStartId="4.[153,190,1281,1300]" captionTargetBox="[227,1050,221,1263]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[227,1050,219,1269]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–6. 1 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) phobos sp. nov., holotype, 4.3 mm; 2 – the same, allotype, 3.7 mm; 3 – the same, aedeagus, holotype; 4 – A. (H.) deimos sp. nov., holotype, 4.3 mm; 5 – the same, allotype, 3.7 mm; 6 – the same, aedeagus, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316396" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316396/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Figs 3, 6</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FD2769155419CAF" blockId="2.[151,1127,323,986]" box="[204,795,963,986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">– median lobe with sparse, fine, dorsolateral serrations.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7145BFFCBFF972FAB76A0544E9BFC" blockId="2.[151,1127,1010,1162]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
The species-group can be simply attributed to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C686FD8FFCBFF972C2776A055969B7F" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" box="[825,972,1010,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B91CC849FFCBFF972C2776A055969B7F" box="[825,972,1010,1034]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Haplanthaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the general body-shape, morphology of the elytral margins and the form of the elytral epipleura at subhumeral part. The species-group is defined by the complete set of the above mentioned characters since each of them separately can be found also in other species-groups and not only in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C686FD8FFCBFF972E64712054579BFF" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" box="[378,525,1138,1162]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B91CC849FFCBFF972E64712054579BFF" box="[378,525,1138,1162]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Haplanthaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
